[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #479 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Electric/Ghost Pokémon.
Rotom has a body of plasma and is shaped like a lightning rod. There is a whitish blue aura of electricity around it that forms lightning bolt-shaped appendages. It has teeth, and its unique, blue eyes have a dividing line across them.

It has the ability to change its form and type by possessing an [[electric fan]], [[refrigerator]], [[microwave]], [[lawnmower]], or [[washing machine]].

Additionally, it possesses the Pokédex and becomes a Rotom Dex, or possesses a cellphone and becomes a Rotom Phone. These forms aid the Trainer but are not usable in battle.

title: synchro_summon
body:
A synchro summon is a method of summoning monsters in [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]].

Introduced in [[Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's]], a synchro summon combines a "tuner" monster with another non-tuner monster to form a "synchro" monster. For example, if you control a level-4 Tuner monster and a level 4 non-Tuner monster, you can combine them to form a level-8 Synchro monster. Only 1 Tuner monster can be used for a single Synchro summon, but multiple non-Tuner monsters may be used.

In the anime, you will notice a green ring surrounding the non-Tuner monster(s). The synchro monster is then formed.

h4. External links

* "Yu-Gi-Oh! Wikia: Synchro Summon":[http://yugioh.wikia.com/wiki/Synchro_Summon]

title: seaport_princess
body:
Seaport Princess is an enemy found in [[Kantai Collection]]. She was the boss of the third event map during the Spring 2014 event.

She is depicted with [[very long hair|very long]] [[white hair|white]] hair, [[red eyes]], large [[claws|clawed]] hands, [[large breasts|a magnificent bust]] and a [[single horn]], and wears a [[short dress|short]] [[ribbed dress]]. Usually depicted as extremely tall and with a soft and shy personality. The second tag, "Great Busty Fortress" is a nod to her buxom figure.

Occasionally called Darwin-chan as a reference to "Port Darwin":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bombing_of_Darwin.

With the addition of [[Northern Ocean Princess]], fans often portray her as an older-sister figure, as they are both harbors. 

Voiced by [[Ogura Yui]].

title: mirim
body:
[b]Mirim[/b] (ミリム) is a [[Queen's Blade Rebellion]] character. Voiced by [[Toyosaki Aki]], designed by [[Tsurugi Hagane]]. She has [[blue eyes]] and [[blue hair]] tied into a braid. She dresses as a valkyrie with armor and a feathered helmet and fights with a spiked shield and a [[chainsword]].

Mirim was an ordinary, timid village girl who moved to the city to raise money and support her family. Lured by the promise of a fat paycheck, she agreed to become a test subject for [[ymir_(queen's_blade)|Ymir's]] research into "the ultimate weapons and armor".

Her sword, shield and armor make use of the vibrating-crystal technology that Ymir developed; they are more than powerful enough to offset the fact that their wielder is completely unskilled in combat. However, the armor has one minor design flaw: the positioning of the vibrating crystals can be... distracting to the wearer.

Mirim's combat book: pool #2112

title: battleship_princess
body:
Battleship Princess is an enemy found in [[Kantai Collection]]. She was the boss of the fifth event map during the Fall 2013 event and reappeared as an enemy in the fifth event map during the Spring 2014 event, the sixth map in the Summer 2014, and the third and fourth maps in the Fall 2014 event.

She is depicted with [[very long hair|very long]] [[black hair|black]] hair, [[glowing eyes|glowing]] [[red eyes]] and two [[horns]], and wears a [[short dress|short]] [[black dress]].

Fondly known as "Dyson" by the fanbase. Because, like the vacuum cleaner brand, she "never loses suction", which in this case means facing her is a never-ending drain of one's time, resources and sanity as well as sucking up shots intended to hit the boss.

title: isolated_island_oni
body:
Isolated Island Oni is an enemy [[abyssal ship]] found in [[Kantai Collection]]. She was the boss of the fifth event map during the Spring 2014 event.

She is depicted with [[very long hair|very long]] [[black hair|black]] hair, [[glowing eyes|glowing]] [[red eyes]], [[small breasts]], two [[horns]], a [[bonnet]], and a frilled [[gothic lolita]] dress with detached sleeves. She also wears [[bodystocking]] and has two spikes protruding from her upper back like [[Airfield Princess]].

She's often portrayed as a [[hikikomori]] in fanart ([i]Isolated[/i] Island Oni). Her nickname amongst fans is "Ritou" (りとう) which is taken from the first two kanji in her name. Also, before [[Northern Ocean Princess]] was introduced, she was the youngest looking [[abyssal ship]], looking more like a 14-15 year old in comparison to the rest of the abyssal fleet whom look 18 and older. In fact because of this she originally had the Pixiv tag "敵艦隊のチャイドル ([i]Teki kantai no chaidoru[/i], lit. "Enemy fleet's child idol") before it was nearly taken over by [[Northern Ocean Princess]].

She is based on "Wake Island":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Wake_Island and is voiced by [[Ogura Yui]].

title: anchorage_water_oni
body:
Anchorage Water Oni is an enemy [[abyssal ship]] in [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i]. She appeared as part of the Spring 2015 Event.

She is essentially an evolved [[Anchorage Oni]] visually. She has very long black hair that [[gradient hair|gradients]] into white and orange eyes. She wears a white dress with an [[overskirt]]. Other than the curved-back horns on her head and the standard abyssal white skin and glowing eyes, she is completely humanoid as shown in her official damaged portrait where her monstrous base is destroyed in which her legs are usually inserted in, and they are completely normal and show that she wears [[high heels]]. The monstrous base she is mounted on is similar to Anchorage Oni's, except now it has more turrets and has developed back legs.

She has a rather masochistic line in-game: "フフッ…イタイ……イタイワ…ウッフフフフフフ… ([i]Fufu....it hurts...it hurts...ufufufufufufu...)[/i]".

title: pt_imp_group
body:
A [[abyssal ship]] enemy type in [[Kantai Collection]].

Representing "PT boats":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PT_boat], which are too small a class for "shipgirlification", they appear as a trio of abyssal [[baby|babies]] or even fetuses whose heads fuse into smaller versions of abyssal destroyer-types, like the [[I-class destroyer]] with large horns. One even has an apparent "[[umbilical cord]]" tube and a black [[diaper]]-like armor.

Like the ships they represent, they carry [[torpedo|torpedoes]] as their primary armament.  In-game they are made to be much harder for larger ships like battleships to hit unless they are armed with secondary guns, as they are meant to represent swarms of tiny coastal craft rather than individual ships. 

They were introduced in the Fall 2015 event, which notably involves battles in the "Solomon Islands Campaign":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solomon_Islands_campaign where the US tried on several occasions to sink Japanese convoys with PT boat torpedo attacks, usually with unsuccessful results. They were quite successful though at "barge busting", attacking the barges and transports in the littorals as they tried to ferry supplies and reinforcements under the cover of night to avoid Allied air superiority.  This helped to cause severe shortages of supplies and reinforcements for Japanese forces.

Their name can literally be read as "small oni group", so they might be considered similar to "oni-tier" ships.

body:
An alternate version of [[Kayle (league of legends)|]] from [[League of Legends]], as she appears in the band [[Pentakill_(league_of_legends)|]].

A golden warrior goddess from a strife-torn world, [[Kayle (league of legends)|]] arrived in Runeterra on the back of a glittering, serpentine dragon. She searches for allies to fight an epic war against the diabolical hordes of her faithless sister. Planet Earth had failed to produce warriors of mettle, so she travelled to Runeterra in search of warriors of metal. Communicating via grand, symphonic metal operas, the depthless sorrow of her arias pierce the hearts of all who hear them. Literally.

title: kuss
body:
A poem by Franz Grillparzer (1791–1872).


[i]Auf die Hände küßt die Achtung,
Freundschaft auf die offne Stirn,
Auf die Wange Wohlgefallen,
Sel'ge Liebe auf den Mund;
Aufs geschloßne Aug' die Sehnsucht,
In die hohle Hand Verlangen,
Arm und Nacken die Begierde;
Überall sonst hin Raserei.[/i]


Respect kisses on the hands,
Friendship on the open forehead,
Delight on the cheek,
Happy love on the mouth;
Longing on the closed eye,
Yearning in the cupped hand,
On arms and neck, desire;
Everywhere else, frenzy.

title: berserker_armor
body:
In [[Berserk]], the Berserker Armor is a cursed suit of [[armor]] that grants its user incredible strength and endurance by allowing its wearer to bypass the normal subconscious limits that prevent him from injuring himself when using his full strength. It can temporarily fix injuries by binding bleeding wounds, reinforcing broken bones and fixing dislocated joints. It can also send its user into a berserker rage where he cannot tell friend from foe. Long-term use of the armor can cause chronic mental deterioration, as well as severe physical effects.

When in Berserker mode, the armor takes on the appearance of the user's inner "beast." For [[Guts (berserk)|]], the current wearer and user of the armor, this is the [[Beast of Darkness (berserk)|]], the demonic hellhound-like wolf that represents all the hatred and evil that dwells within his soul, which becomes stronger every time Guts uses the armor.

title: beast_of_darkness_(berserk)
body:
In [[Berserk]], the Beast of Darkness, also known as the Hellhound, is [[Guts (berserk)|]]' inner beast, the manifestation of all the hatred and evil that has dwelled within his soul since the Eclipse. It takes the form of a great black houndlike wolf with sinister-looking flaming red eyes. It taunts him, questioning the morality of his quest for revenge against [[Griffith (berserk)|]] and urging him to commit ever-greater atrocities, with the ultimate goal of turning him into a monster.

As the Black Swordsman, Guts and the Beast worked in concert, and the path of revenge and bloodshed that Guts walked after the Eclipse allowed the Beast to grow in power. When Guts found [[Casca (berserk)|]] again and started thinking about things other than revenge, the Beast began to work against him, and has begun attempting to convince him to give into his dark desires and kill her so that he can get back to his vendetta against Griffith. The [[Berserker Armor]], though it increases Guts' fighting power against the demonic Apostles that he fights, gives power to the Beast every time he goes into Berserker mode, and only with the help of his newfound friends has Guts managed to keep the Beast at bay.

title: mozgus_(berserk)
body: In [[Berserk]], Mozgus is the chief inquisitor of the Holy See in Albion. A crazy religious fanatic, his zealous purging of Albion's slums would spread a shadow of fear over the city. [[Guts (berserk)|]] ends up having to fight him after he and his Holy Iron Chain Knights mistake the maddened [[Casca (berserk)|]] for a witch.

title: puck_(berserk)
body: In [[Berserk]], Puck is one of the Elves, diminutive fairy-like creatures who have the power to heal others. Since his rescue by [[Guts (berserk)|]] from the bandits of Koka Castle, he's taken to following the Black Swordsman around, healing him during his many battles with the Apostles and acting as his conscience.

title: brand_of_sacrifice
body: The Brand of Sacrifice is the symbol of the Godhand in [[Berserk]], and marks those chosen to be sacrificed. The Brand acts as a beacon for ravenous demons who want to eat the bearer alive, and it bleeds and causes pain whenever they draw near. [[Guts (berserk)|]] has his Brand on the back of his neck, while [[Casca (berserk)|]] has hers on her left breast. The two are the only known characters of the series to have survived being branded.

title: ushiromiya_beatrice
body:
[b]Major spoilers below.[/b]

Character from [[Umineko no Naku Koro ni]].

[spoiler]Ushiromiya Beatrice (often referred to as Kuwadorian Beatrice) was the daughter of [[Ushiromiya Kinzou]] and [[Beatrice Castiglioni]]. Kinzo named her after her mother, who died giving birth to her, claiming Kuwadorian Beatrice to be the reincarnation of his dead lover. She lived in the hidden Kuwadorian mansion on Rokkenjima, where she was raised by [[Kumasawa Chiyo]].

As she grew older, her appearance was strikingly similar to that of her dead mother. Kinzo did not see her as his daughter, and poured his affection onto her, resulting in the birth of [[Yasu_(umineko)|]]/[[ushiromiya_lion|Lion]].

Kuwadorian Beatrice later met her death when [[Ushiromiya Rosa]] chanced upon the mansion and took her outside, where she fell off a cliff and died. She is the basis of the legend of the Golden Witch and is the model for the portrait in the main hall.[/spoiler]

title: black_dragon_(power_rangers)
body:
Black Dragon is a controlled [[mecha|zord-like machine]] from the [[Mighty Morphin Power Rangers]] comic.

The Green Chaos crystal that [[Witch Bandora|Rita Repulsa]] gave Scorpina became charged with green chaos energy it collected from fighting Tommy. When Tommy, Jason, and Zack started arguing at the Command Center, the crystal opened a portal (and blew up half the Center) allowing the Black Dragon to emerge in a gigantic size. He shrunk down and confronted the rangers, offering them a chance to surrender but they refused. He walked right through the rangers, seemingly trying to drain their powers every chance he got. Most of the rangers escaped Black Dragon in the pocket dimension but he managed to grab Billy and knock him out. When Rita and her forces arrived at the wreckage, Black Dragon used Billy's power coin and the Green Chaos crystal to tap directly into the Morphin Grid and absorb Jason, Zack, Trini, and Kimberly's powers.

It later turned out that the Black Dragon was a zord-like machine, reconstructed using parts from the [[Dragonzord]], controlled by [[Lord Drakkon]].

title: fu-ha_jin
body:
Fu-ha Jin is a strange looking ninja first appearing [[Ryuuko no Ken]] Gaiden (Art of Fighting 3). He was a disciple of the Kisaragi school of ninjutsu until he was passed over for [[Kisaragi Eiji]] as the sole successor to be leader. Jin left in anger and decided to wait for his opportunity to destroy Eiji, and at the same time decided to fight Eiji's rival [[Ryou Sakazaki]].

He had little notability until re-discovered by Japanese website Bohyou, which led to the Japanese [[m.u.g.e.n|MUGEN]] community finding him and frequently using him. His odd looking moves and memetic lines led to his popularity as a joke character.

This, in turn, has led him to appear in MUGEN related works such as  [i][[The Iron of Yin and Yang|Touhou - The Iron of Yin and Yang]][/i], where he is the only non-[[Touhou]], non-[[Final Fantasy XI]] character.

title: chris_(kof)
body:
Character from [[the King of Fighters]] series of fighting games.

He is the singer for CYS, a rock band consisting of and named after the initals of himself (C), [[Nanakase Yashiro]] (Y), and [[Shermie (kof)|]] (S).

They seemingly entered [[The King Of Fighters '97|The 1997 King of Fighters tournament]] to take revenge on [[Yagami Iori]] for canceling one or more of their shows, but as the tournament progresses, their Orochi blood awakens, thus remembering their status as the Four Heavenly Kings of [[Orochi_(kof)|]] alongside [[Goenitz]].

Shermie and Yashiro sacrifice themselves to awaken Orochi, who would later use him as a vessel. But Orochi's awakening was short-lived as [[Kusanagi Kyou|Kusanagi Kyo]] (possessing the Sword of the Kusanagi), Iori (possessing the Jewel of Yasakani, and the target of CYS), and [[Kagura Chizuru]] (possessing the Mirror of Yata) combine forces to seal Orochi along with Chris's body.

He fights using speedy attacks in his normal form, and [[purple fire]] as [[Orochi Chris]].

[[The King Of Fighters]] character. She is famous for her hair that is tied into split ponytails with [[Hair over eyes|bangs that cover her eyes]] and large bust. She is the keyboardist for CYS, a rock band consisting of and named after the initals of [[Chris (kof)|]] (C), [[Nanakase Yashiro]] (Y), and herself (S).

They seemingly entered [[The King Of Fighters '97|The 1997 King of Fighters tournament]] to take revenge on [[Yagami Iori]] for canceling one or more of their shows, but as the tournament progresses, their Orochi blood awakens, thus remembering their status as the Four Heavenly Kings of [[Orochi (kof)|]] alongside [[Goenitz]].

title: deneb_rove
body:
Deneb Rhode is a Witch♥. She is a recurring character from the [[Ogre Battle]]/[[Tactics Ogre]] games, and has appeared in every installment of the series.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair|blonde]] or [[orange hair|orange]] hair (depending on the game), and a [[cleavage|generous bust shown off by her choice of clothing]]. She is usually shown wearing a [[purple dress|purple]] [[strapless dress|strapless]] [[microdress]], [[purple gloves|purple]] [[elbow gloves]], [[purple footwear|purple]] [[high heel boots|heeled]] [[thigh boots]] (or [[ankle boots]] in some games), and of course, a [[witch hat|witch's hat]] (also [[purple headwear|purple]]). Occasionally, she smokes a [[kiseru]]. 

Deneb [i]loves[/i] [[pumpkins]], and has even created [[pumpkinhead (ogre battle)|pumpkin-headed minions]] to serve and assist her. She also owns an item [[shop]] where she sells, among other things, candy armor and [[glass pumpkin|glass pumpkins]].

title: alain_(pokemon)
body:

Supporting character in the [[Pokemon XY (anime)|Pokemon XY anime]] series, and lead character in [i]The Strongest Mega Evolution[/i] side story arc. Alain is an aloof Pokémon Trainer seeking to defeat all Mega Evolved Pokémon with his partner, a Charizard that can Mega Evolve into [[Mega Charizard X]].

Initially an assistant to [[Augustine Sycamore]], he traveled with [[Mairin (pokemon)|]], a novice Trainer. He is working with [[Lysandre (pokemon)|]], who led him to believe he can protect Sycamore and Mairin by pursuing [[Zygarde]]. title: underground_(sinnoh)
body:
The Underground is a large area comprised of many corridors located underneath the whole region of Sinnoh, accessible in [i][[Pokemon DPPt|Pokémon Diamond, Pearl and Platinum]][/i].

Multiple players can interact in the Underground via the DS Wireless Communication.

Some activities available in the Undergound include:

* Digging items such as fossils and evolutionary stones from the walls.
* Building and decorating a [[secret_base_(pokemon)|Secret Base]].
* Finding the Secret Bases of other players and capturing their flags.
* Placing traps on the ground, which often negatively affect the movements of players who step on them.

See post #3364990 for a piece of [[official art]] depicting the Underground.

title: pokemon_go
body:
A mobile app created by Niantic, Inc. and the Pokemon Company. Players take their smartphones with them, walk around, and catch [[Pokemon]], just like in the main series. The game initially included Generation I Pokemon, but began adding Generation II Pokemon in early 2017 and Generation III during the same year's Halloween event.

The game is often set as an example of a "flavor of the month" fad. Its online popularity dropped drastically a few months after its release; many blame this on the lack of updates and content on launch, Niantic, Inc.'s poor management and playerbase communication, and its freemium pay-to-win system prevalent in many other mobile games. However, despite the decrease in internet activity, it's still a popular game, and some cite the game and the release of [i][[pokemon sm|Pokemon Sun and Moon]][/i] as the causes of a resurgence in franchise popularity overall. More features being added over the course of 2017 have also drawn back some of the initial fans that dropped off for the above reasons.
